---
export const prerender = false;
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { COMPANY } from "../config/company";
import { getSupabaseAdmin } from "../lib/supabase";

// Hardcoded fallback FAQ items grouped by section
const fallbackFaqs = {
  getting_started: [
    { question: "How do I know if AI is actually right for my business?", answer: "Honest answer: it depends on what you're trying to fix. AI works well when you have repetitive tasks that eat up staff time, decisions that rely on data you're already collecting, or customer interactions that happen at volume. It doesn't work well when your core processes are broken or undefined. AI will just automate the mess faster. We won't take your money if we don't think AI will help. We say that in every first call and we mean it." },
    { question: "What size company do you usually work with?", answer: "Most of our clients have between 15 and 300 employees. They're established enough to have real processes to automate, but small enough that they can't afford a dedicated in-house AI team. We've worked with companies as small as 8 people and as large as 600. The question isn't size. It's whether you have a clear business problem that AI can solve." },
    { question: "Do I need technical staff on my team for this to work?", answer: "No. We've built systems for family businesses run entirely by non-technical people. You'll need someone who understands your business well enough to explain it to us. That's it. We handle the technical side. What we do ask is that you have at least one internal champion: someone who will push adoption within the team, answer our questions quickly, and take ownership of the system after we hand it over." },
    { question: "How is this different from using a general AI tool?", answer: "A general AI tool doesn't know your products, your pricing, your customers, or your tone. It can't connect to your CRM, update your records, or notify your team in real time. What we build is trained on your data, connected to your systems, and built to do one job very well: the specific job you're hiring it for. Think of it like the difference between a temp worker and a full-time specialist who only does one thing but does it perfectly." },
    { question: "What happens in the first meeting?", answer: "It's a 30-minute call. We'll ask you about your biggest operational headache, what tools you currently use, and roughly what budget you're working with. Then we'll be honest about whether AI can help, what it might look like, and what it would cost. You won't get a sales pitch. You'll get a direct assessment. If there's no fit, we'll tell you that too, and often point you toward something that would actually work." },
  ],
  guarantee: [
    { question: "How does the 100% refund guarantee actually work?", answer: "Simple: if we deliver the agreed system and your team genuinely isn't satisfied with it, we refund everything you paid. The guarantee covers the full project cost, not just a partial refund. We have to agree upfront on what \"success\" means for your project (specific metrics, deliverables, outcomes). If we hit those and you still want a refund, we'll discuss it. If we don't hit them, there's no discussion needed." },
    { question: "Has anyone ever actually claimed the refund?", answer: "No. And that's partly because we're selective about which projects we take. We turn down projects we don't think will work, not because we don't want the revenue, but because a failed project hurts everyone. The guarantee keeps us honest: if we weren't confident in our work, offering a full refund wouldn't make business sense." },
    { question: "What if we change direction halfway through?", answer: "It happens. Business needs change. If you want to change scope mid-project, we have an honest conversation about what that means for cost and timeline. Small changes are usually absorbed. Major pivots get a revised scope document. If at any point you decide you don't want to continue, you pay for work completed to that point. We don't chase you for the full amount. We'd rather have a fair conversation than a legal one." },
    { question: "What's the catch? Why would you offer this?", answer: "No catch. AI projects in the UAE have a reputation problem: too many companies have been burned by consultants who disappeared after delivery, or by vendors that sounded impressive in a demo but never worked in practice. We needed a way to show we're different. Offering a full refund was the most direct way to say: we are that confident. If that confidence turns out to be wrong in your case, you shouldn't pay for it." },
  ],
  technical: [
    { question: "Is our business data safe? Where does it go?", answer: "Your data doesn't leave the systems we agree on at the start. We work within UAE data residency requirements and we map out every data flow before writing a line of code. You sign a clear NDA before we see anything sensitive. The AI systems we build process your data. They don't store it in ways that expose you. We can walk through the specific data architecture for your project in the first call if this is a concern." },
    { question: "Does it connect to our existing software?", answer: "Usually yes. We connect to most CRM platforms, ERP systems, messaging tools, e-commerce platforms, and property management systems. If you're on a less common system, we'll check if it has an API. Most business software does. If it doesn't, we'll tell you that upfront rather than discovering it mid-project." },
    { question: "What happens if the AI gives wrong or embarrassing answers?", answer: "This is the right question to ask. Customer-facing AI needs guardrails. Every system we build has a fallback: if the AI can't answer with confidence, it routes the query to a human instead of guessing. We also do structured testing before going live, trying to break it with edge cases before your customers get the chance to. For the first 30 days after launch, you have direct access to us to flag anything that doesn't look right. We fix it fast." },
    { question: "Can it actually handle Arabic, or is it just an afterthought?", answer: "It's not an afterthought. It's part of the core build. Our team works in Arabic, and we test Arabic responses the same way we test English ones. The AI understands Gulf Arabic, code-switching (mixing English and Arabic in one message), and the specific tone customers expect in different contexts. A lot of AI vendors in Dubai say they support Arabic but don't actually test it under real conditions. We do." },
    { question: "What AI models do you use? Do we get locked into one provider?", answer: "We work with multiple AI model providers and pick the right one for each use case. Most systems we build are model-agnostic by design, meaning we can swap out the underlying model if a better one comes along or if pricing changes. You won't find yourself stuck paying more because one provider raised its rates." },
  ],
};

let gettingStartedFaqs = fallbackFaqs.getting_started;
let guaranteeFaqs = fallbackFaqs.guarantee;
let technicalFaqs = fallbackFaqs.technical;

try {
  const supabase = getSupabaseAdmin();
  const { data, error } = await supabase
    .from('faq_items')
    .select('question, answer, section, sort_order')
    .eq('published', true)
    .in('section', ['getting_started', 'guarantee', 'technical'])
    .order('section')
    .order('sort_order');

  if (!error && data && data.length > 0) {
    const gsItems = data.filter(item => item.section === 'getting_started');
    const gItems = data.filter(item => item.section === 'guarantee');
    const tItems = data.filter(item => item.section === 'technical');
    if (gsItems.length > 0) gettingStartedFaqs = gsItems;
    if (gItems.length > 0) guaranteeFaqs = gItems;
    if (tItems.length > 0) technicalFaqs = tItems;
  }
} catch (err) {
  // Fallback to hardcoded content on error
}

Astro.response.headers.set('Cache-Control', 's-maxage=60, stale-while-revalidate=300');

const allFaqs = [...gettingStartedFaqs, ...guaranteeFaqs, ...technicalFaqs];
const faqSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: allFaqs.map(f => ({
    '@type': 'Question',
    name: f.question,
    acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: f.answer },
  })),
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="FAQ: Honest Answers About AI for Your Business | Aegis AI"
  description="Real answers to the questions Dubai businesses ask before starting an AI project. Timeline, the guarantee, and what actually happens during a project."
  canonicalPath="/faq"
  arPath="/ar/faq"
  ldJson={faqSchema}
>

<!-- ── HERO ── -->
<header class="hero-section" style="padding-top: 10rem; padding-bottom: 5rem; text-align: center;">
  <div class="container" style="position: relative; z-index: 1;">
    <div style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:4px;background:rgba(0,227,253,0.12);border:1px solid rgba(0,227,253,0.28);border-radius:100px;padding:6px 16px;color:#004f58;font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:1.5rem;" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:none;opacity:0.65;">Home</a><span style="opacity:0.4;padding:0 4px;"> / </span>FAQ</div>
    <div style="display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: .5rem; background: #e7eeff; color: #00253b; font-size: .8rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: .05em; padding: .375rem 1rem; border-radius: 100px; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" class="w-4 h-4" stroke="#006875" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M9.09 9a3 3 0 015.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3"/><path d="M12 17h.01"/></svg>
      Frequently Asked Questions
    </div>
    <h1 style="max-width: 44rem; margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;">
      Questions before you book?<br>
      <span class="gradient-text">Good. Here are honest answers.</span>
    </h1>
    <p style="color: #42474e; font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.75; max-width: 38rem; margin: 0 auto 2.5rem;">
      We get variations of the same questions in every discovery call. We figured we'd answer them here so you can come prepared, or decide we're not the right fit before spending 30 minutes on a call.
    </p>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; gap: .75rem;">
      <a href="#" class="faq-tab">Getting Started</a>
      <a href="#" class="faq-tab">The Guarantee</a>
      <a href="#" class="faq-tab">Technical & Data</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- HERO IMAGE -->
<div style="position:relative; overflow:hidden; height:240px;">
  <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1573164574511-73c773193279?w=1400&q=80&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Common questions about AI for business" loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" width="1400" height="240" style="width:100%; height:100%; object-fit:cover; object-position:center 30%;" />
  <div style="position:absolute; inset:0; background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(0,104,117,0.20),rgba(0,37,59,0.45));"></div>
</div>

<!-- ── GETTING STARTED ── -->
<section id="getting-started" class="section" aria-labelledby="gs-heading">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 48rem;">
    <div class="category-label">Getting Started</div>
    <h2 id="gs-heading" class="category-heading">Before you commit to anything</h2>
    {gettingStartedFaqs.map((item) => (
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-btn" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false">{item.question}<span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" class="w-3 h-3" stroke="#006875" stroke-width="3"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-body">{item.answer}</div></div>
    ))}
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── THE GUARANTEE ── -->
<section id="guarantee" class="section" aria-labelledby="guar-heading">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 48rem;">
    <div class="category-label" style="color: #92400e;">The Guarantee</div>
    <h2 id="guar-heading" class="category-heading">The 100% refund: how it actually works</h2>
    <div class="guarantee-box">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="#F59E0B" class="w-8 h-8 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><path d="M12 1L3 5v6c0 5.25 3.75 10.15 9 11.25C17.25 21.15 21 16.25 21 11V5l-9-4z"/></svg>
      <div>
        <h4 style="color: #00253b; margin-bottom: .5rem;">If you don't love what we build, you pay nothing.</h4>
        <p style="color: #92400e;">We're the only AI company in the UAE that offers a full refund on a completed project. Here's why we can do that, and why it's never been claimed.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    {guaranteeFaqs.map((item) => (
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-btn" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false">{item.question}<span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" class="w-3 h-3" stroke="#006875" stroke-width="3"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-body">{item.answer}</div></div>
    ))}
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── TECHNICAL & DATA ── -->
<section id="technical" class="section" style="background: #e7eeff;" aria-labelledby="tech-heading">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 48rem;">
    <div class="category-label">Technical & Data</div>
    <h2 id="tech-heading" class="category-heading">The practical questions about how it works</h2>
    {technicalFaqs.map((item) => (
      <div class="faq-item" style="border-bottom-color: #c2c7ce;"><button class="faq-btn" style="background: transparent;" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false">{item.question}<span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" class="w-3 h-3" stroke="#006875" stroke-width="3"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-body">{item.answer}</div></div>
    ))}
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── STILL HAVE QUESTIONS ── -->
<section class="section-sm" aria-label="Call to action">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 44rem;">
    <div class="card text-center">
      <div style="width: 56px; height: 56px; border-radius: 16px; background: #e7eeff; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" class="w-7 h-7" stroke="#006875" stroke-width="1.8"><path d="M21 15a2 2 0 01-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 012-2h14a2 2 0 012 2z"/></svg>
      </div>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Still have a question we didn't answer?</h2>
      <p style="color: #42474e; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.7; max-width: 28rem; margin: 0 auto 2rem;">Book a 30-minute call. We'll give you straight answers and tell you honestly if we think working together makes sense.</p>
      <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center;">
        <button onclick="openModal(this)" data-source="faq_cta" class="btn-primary">Book a Free Call →</button>
        <a href={`https://wa.me/${COMPANY.whatsapp}`} class="btn-outline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" class="w-4 h-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M21 11.5a8.38 8.38 0 01-.9 3.8 8.5 8.5 0 01-7.6 4.7 8.38 8.38 0 01-3.8-.9L3 21l1.9-5.7a8.38 8.38 0 01-.9-3.8 8.5 8.5 0 014.7-7.6 8.38 8.38 0 013.8-.9h.5a8.48 8.48 0 018 8v.5z"/></svg>
          Message on WhatsApp
        </a>
      </div>
      <p style="color: #72787e; font-size: .875rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">No commitment. No pitch. Just answers.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@graph": [
    {
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "How do I know if AI is actually right for my business?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "It depends on what you're trying to fix. AI works well when you have repetitive tasks that eat up staff time, decisions that rely on data you're already collecting, or customer interactions that happen at volume." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What does it actually cost to work with you?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "All pricing is customized to your specific project, scope, and team size. Book a free discovery call and we will give you an honest, clear quote." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "How does the 100% refund guarantee work?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "If we deliver the agreed system and your team genuinely isn't satisfied, we refund everything you paid. We agree upfront on success metrics." } }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://aegisai.ae/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "FAQ", "item": "https://aegisai.ae/pages/faq.html" }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
</script>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
.faq-tab {
      display: inline-flex; align-items: center;
      padding: .625rem 1.25rem; border-radius: 100px;
      font-size: .875rem; font-weight: 600; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
      border: 1px solid #c2c7ce; color: #42474e; background: #ffffff;
      cursor: pointer; text-decoration: none;
      transition: border-color .2s, color .2s, background .2s;
    }
    .faq-tab:hover, .faq-tab.active {
      border-color: #006875; color: #006875; background: rgba(0,104,117,0.06);
    }
    .category-label {
      font-size: .75rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: .08em;
      text-transform: uppercase; color: #006875;
      font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; margin-bottom: .75rem;
    }
    .category-heading { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
    .guarantee-box {
      background: rgba(245,158,11,0.07);
      border: 1px solid rgba(245,158,11,0.28);
      border-radius: 20px; padding: 1.75rem 2rem;
      display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }
</style>